{%- comment -%}
  Product Recommendations ("You may also like")
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Rendered via Shopify's Section Rendering API — NOT placed in any product
  template JSON directly. The PDP contains a `[data-component="product-
  recommendations"]` placeholder; the `productRecommendations` TS component
  fetches this section via:

    /recommendations/products
      ?section_id=product-recommendations
      &product_id=<id>
      &limit=12
      &intent=related

  Shopify populates the `recommendations` object only in the context of that
  URL. On initial page render (no such URL), `recommendations.performed` is
  false and this section renders empty — the placeholder stays a no-op.

  Visual: reuses the `scroll-section` + `scroll-arrows` pattern from
  `product-as-seen-on.liquid` so both share one horizontal-scroll UX.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- if recommendations.performed and recommendations.products_count > 0 -%}
  <div
    data-component="scroll-section"
    data-product-recommendations-content
    class="flex flex-col gap-4 px-2 py-10 lg:py-16"
  >
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
      {%- comment -%}
        Section heading — bumped from 12px (info-row scale) to 16px
        medium so the rail reads as a section separator, not a PDP
        form label. Tracking matches the other uppercase labels on the
        page (info accordion rows, variant picker labels) so the
        typographic system stays consistent.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <h2 class="text-[16px] font-medium text-fg uppercase tracking-[0.3px]">
        {{ 'products.recommendations.title' | t }}
      </h2>
      {% if recommendations.products_count > 4 %}
        {% render 'scroll-arrows' %}
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    <div
      class="flex gap-1 overflow-x-auto overflow-y-hidden snap-x snap-mandatory no-scrollbar"
      data-scroll-container
    >
      {%- for recommended_product in recommendations.products -%}
        <div class="w-[calc(50%-2px)] lg:w-[calc(25%-3px)] shrink-0 snap-start">
          {%- render 'product-card', product: recommended_product -%}
        </div>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  This section is only ever rendered via the Section Rendering API — it's
  never placed in a template JSON, so theme-editor settings here would be
  unreachable. `limit` and `intent` are controlled by the placeholder URL
  query params in `sections/main-product.liquid` instead.
{%- endcomment -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Product Recommendations",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
